 BARELY 24 hours after gunmen killed Nasarawa State chairman of the All Progressives Congress (APC), two persons have been abducted and another shot dead in the state. The latest attack took place in Agwada, headquarters of Agwada Development Area. Gunmen stormed the house of one Alhaji Kankau about 2am on Sunday, and took away two of his children, a source said, adding that one of Kankauâ€™s sons was killed in the attack. Two of his wives have been hospitalised after being hurt during the attack. Chairman of Kokona council Saidu Kurki confirmed the incident but declined further comments. 